1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,920
[Marcus] <i>I don't believe General Carillo</i>
<i>had nothing to do with this.</i>

2
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:06,381
[Jalil] <i>But we don't have</i>
<i>any evidence against him.</i>

3
00:00:06,464 --> 00:00:08,466
You need to stay close to the General.

4
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:11,302
Find out his whereabouts.

5
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:15,181
Did you notice those subtle glances
between General Carillo and Felix earlier?

6
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:17,475
[Jalil]
<i>Yes. It felt like they meant something.</i>

7
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:18,727
<i>Do you think…</i>

8
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:22,063
<i>Felix has anything to do</i>
<i>with what the General's been doing?</i>

9
00:00:22,981 --> 00:00:23,898
[Marcus] <i>I don't know yet.</i>

10
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:27,777
But starting now, we need
to keep Felix under surveillance.

11
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:31,197
[Felix] <i>I told her so many times</i>
<i>but she didn't listen to me.</i>

12
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:33,533
Lara… Wherever you are…

13
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:35,410
I'm sorry.

14
00:00:35,493 --> 00:00:37,412
- [phone ringing]
- Jamilah? What is it?

15
00:00:37,495 --> 00:00:41,875
I just heard what happened to…
your teammate Lara Angeles.

16
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:43,126
[Jamilah] <i>Why was she killed?</i>

17
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:45,211
[Jalil] <i>We're still figuring it out.</i>
<i>Why are you asking?</i>

18
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:48,214
I'm just worried about you, Jalil.

19
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:49,674
How is Father doing?

20
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:51,259
[Datu Rahman] <i>My child, please.</i>

21
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:55,305
<i>Let me tell Jalil</i>
<i>about all of this myself.</i>

22
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:57,640
Jalil, why don't you pay Father a visit?

23
00:00:58,266 --> 00:00:59,893
It sounds like you have
a lot to talk about.

24
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:02,312
It's dangerous
if someone sees us together.

25
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:04,647
I don't know
if someone's keeping an eye on me.

26
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:07,192
[Usman]
I watched Maya Mae Kalaw's documentary.

27
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:10,028
Apparently, Mustapha and General Carillo

28
00:01:10,111 --> 00:01:11,529
are going to face each other
in a live interview.

29
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:13,531
That's your chance.

30
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:15,075
[Azuelo] <i>After that,</i>

31
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:19,496
<i>they'll definitely move forward</i>
<i>with all their evil plans.</i>

32
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:22,082
Stay alert. Things are getting heated.

33
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:24,918
The massacre on Damai Island,

34
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:27,879
<i>the bank robbery, the school shooting,</i>

35
00:01:27,962 --> 00:01:30,882
<i>the hostage taking, the bombing</i>
<i>targeting the Japanese tourists,</i>

36
00:01:30,965 --> 00:01:34,385
<i>now, the recent death</i>
<i>of Agent Lara Angeles,</i>

37
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:35,970
<i>are they all connected?</i>

38
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:39,307
[Manuel]
<i>My daughter Lara was one of the casualties</i>

39
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:41,851
<i>of all this chaos.</i>

40
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:45,772
Crimes nowadays have simply
gone out of hand.

41
00:01:45,855 --> 00:01:47,440
Injustice continues to prevail.

42
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:49,025
General, with all due respect,

43
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:53,279
there is a bigger reason
this is happening.

44
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:56,324
[Mustapha]
<i>It all started with the explosion…</i>

45
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:59,661
on the MV Doña Emilia.

46
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:01,329
[tense music playing]

47
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:11,589
[theme music playing]

48
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:27,939
A lot of people died during that incident.

49
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:34,279
[Mustapha] <i>Many say…</i>

50
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,782
<i>that it was an accident.</i>

51
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:39,742
But the truth is…

52
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:42,912
the police found out

53
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:47,000
that the ship was carrying
illegal firearms.

54
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:49,210
[suspenseful music playing]

55
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:56,718
When they were about to capture it,

56
00:02:57,844 --> 00:02:59,304
the ship exploded.

57
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:02,557
Hundreds of people died.

58
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:05,935
Even the illegal firearms
that could point back

59
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:06,853
to the syndicate

60
00:03:08,187 --> 00:03:09,606
sank deep into the water.

61
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:12,567
Now tell me that the ship
wasn't deliberately

62
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:15,695
detonated to make it sink.

63
00:03:15,778 --> 00:03:17,780
[suspenseful music continues]

64
00:03:26,789 --> 00:03:27,957
[young Marcus] Gabriel!

65
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:37,926
[explosion]

66
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:39,594
[young Marcus groaning]

67
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:44,307
[groans] Gabriel!

68
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:49,562
- [young Gabriel screaming]
- Gabriel, come on, let's go!

69
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,148
[young Gabriel] <i>There's a fire!</i>

70
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:54,108
- [young Gabriel sobbing]
- Ack!

71
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:56,736
[pensive music playig]

72
00:03:56,819 --> 00:03:58,279
DOÑA EMILIA CASE OFFICIALLY CLOSED;
PROBE POINTS TO GAS LEAK

73
00:03:58,363 --> 00:03:59,530
M/V DOÑA EMILIA:
FIRE AT SEA! GAS LEAK OR NEGLIGENCE?

74
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:08,957
[young Teresa sobbing]
<i>Where's my son Gabriel?!</i>

75
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:09,916
<i>Gabriel!</i>

76
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:11,793
<i>Gabriel!</i>

77
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,879
<i>Gabriel! What did you do to him?!</i>

78
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:19,300
[sobbing] Let's just pray for him, please!

79
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:21,386
[sobs]

80
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:24,514
[crying]

81
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:32,897
[stirring music continues]

82
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:52,166
[stirring music continues]

83
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:12,061
[sobbing]

84
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:23,948
[sniffles]

85
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:43,134
[sobbing continues]

86
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:02,195
Doctor?

87
00:06:02,278 --> 00:06:05,323
[Teresa crying softly]

88
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,784
Doc, are you okay?

89
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:11,954
[Teresa crying]

90
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:18,127
I thought it was just an accident.

91
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:19,754
But…

92
00:06:22,256 --> 00:06:26,719
There were people
behind the ship's explosion.

93
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:32,141
They're the ones behind the tragedy
that killed Gabriel.

94
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,560
- [sniffles]
- Doc…

95
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:36,938
And until now…

96
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:39,023
They're still running free.

97
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,901
[Teresa crying]

98
00:06:42,985 --> 00:06:46,948
I've been grieving for my son
for decades, Jamilah.

99
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:51,577
[Teresa breathing deeply]

100
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:52,912
[Teresa crying]

101
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:00,294
[somber music continues]

102
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:09,053
- [plastic rustling]
- [drawer shuts]

103
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:20,106
Gabriel…

104
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:22,984
Gabriel…

105
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:26,737
[Teresa crying]

106
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:31,409
[line ringing]

107
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:39,959
Mustapha knows.

108
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:42,295
We have to get rid of him!

109
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:46,174
Copy, General. Everything is ready.

110
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:48,509
[stirring music playing]

111
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,656
[stirring music continues]

112
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:11,657
[button clicks]

113
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:23,586
[Marcus] Sir--

114
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:27,548
I-It's okay. Leave us for now.

115
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:31,802
Agent Marcus Reyes!
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

116
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,513
[in Arabic] And upon you be peace.

117
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:35,389
Sir…

118
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:38,267
What you said in the interview

119
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,853
about the explosion of MV Doña Emilia…

120
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:43,022
Who was responsible for that?

121
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:46,359
I'm still investigating it.

122
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:50,488
But I'll soon find out who was behind it.

123
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:54,825
[stirring music continues]

124
00:08:55,409 --> 00:08:57,954
But you're certain
that it was not an accident?

125
00:09:00,122 --> 00:09:01,415
Why do you ask?

126
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:04,585
[stirring music continues]

127
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:07,922
My brother died because of that explosion.

128
00:09:13,469 --> 00:09:16,931
What happened to that ship…
was not an accident.

129
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:23,813
MV Emilia was intentionally blown up.

130
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:26,691
[stirring music continues]

131
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:47,920
[stirring music continues]

132
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:17,408
[stirring music continues]

133
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:35,426
[car door opens, closes]

134
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:38,512
[car engine starts]

135
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:58,115
[tense music playing]

136
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,671
[line disconnects]

137
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:17,051
What's happening?

138
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:18,677
Someone's tailing Sir Mustapha.

139
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:21,389
[motorcycle engines revving]

140
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:24,266
His life is in danger.

141
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:26,394
Come on!

142
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:37,154
[line disconnects]

143
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,543
[uneasy music playing]

144
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:54,547
Mustapha is right.

145
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:57,758
[Omar] What do you mean?

146
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:04,473
Jalil is risking his life for me.

147
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:06,434
For the truth.

148
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:12,440
My silence protects no one but me.

149
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:15,693
What's your plan?

150
00:12:16,694 --> 00:12:19,280
I'll tell him the truth, Omar.

151
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:21,365
Even if it's hard.

152
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:28,873
That's the only way I can protect my son.

153
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:40,426
[pensive music playing]

154
00:12:47,057 --> 00:12:51,103
[cellphone ringing]

155
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:55,816
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

156
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:58,110
[Jalil] <i>Sir, someone is following you.</i>

157
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:01,989
[motorcycle revs]

158
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,077
Carillo.

159
00:13:08,829 --> 00:13:09,955
[huffs]

160
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:11,624
Young man.

161
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:14,210
Get ready. We're about
to head into trouble.

162
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:20,007
[grim music playing]

163
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:23,511
[gun clicks]

164
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:26,430
[car revs]

165
00:13:29,058 --> 00:13:32,228
[motorcycle revs]

166
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:39,777
[cellphone ringing]

167
00:13:42,905 --> 00:13:45,491
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.
They don't seem hostile.

168
00:13:48,118 --> 00:13:49,203
[bazooka fires, explosion]

169
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:52,206
[in Arabic] My God!

170
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:55,960
Drive fast.

171
00:13:57,294 --> 00:14:00,047
[gunshots]

172
00:14:04,301 --> 00:14:05,469
Open the door.

173
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:11,350
[tires squealing]

174
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:13,310
[gunshots]

175
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:16,188
[gunshots]

176
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:17,982
[tires squealing]

177
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:19,441
Keep it steady.

178
00:14:20,734 --> 00:14:22,862
[gunshots]

179
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:27,408
[motorcycle revs]

180
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:31,912
[motorcycle revs]

181
00:14:37,626 --> 00:14:38,711
[gunshots]

182
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:43,799
[gunshots]

183
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:45,217
[tires squealing]

184
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,721
Drive fast.

185
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:51,140
[suspenseful music playing]

186
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:52,266
[loading guns]

187
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:53,350
Get down!

188
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:55,686
[rapid gunfire]

189
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:10,993
[rapid gunfire]

190
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:16,457
Get out!

191
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:32,097
[motorcycle revs]

192
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:36,727
[suspenseful music continues]

193
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:41,732
[tires screeching]

194
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:44,109
[explosion]

195
00:15:47,112 --> 00:15:49,156
[gunshots]

196
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:52,076
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

197
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:53,911
[tires screeching]

198
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:02,920
[in Arabic] And unto you peace.

199
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:06,298
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you,
Agent Marcus.

200
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:07,758
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

201
00:16:07,841 --> 00:16:11,178
[suspenseful music continues]

202
00:16:26,276 --> 00:16:28,153
Go ahead, Espina.

203
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:31,240
Why don't you go first?

204
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:33,951
Why don't both of you go?

205
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:41,625
[rapid gunfire]

206
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:18,537
[rapid gunfire]

207
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:21,957
Hold it!

208
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:45,439
[in Arabic] God is great!

209
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:49,151
[in Arabic] God is great!

210
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:52,404
[tense music playing]

211
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:58,243
God is great.

212
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:00,871
[in Arabic] God is great!

213
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:05,501
Agent Marcus,

214
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:06,627
Espina,

215
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:09,254
I'm grateful you guys came.

216
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:10,714
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

217
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:12,966
I need to go to Malacañáng.

218
00:18:13,509 --> 00:18:15,177
I need to talk to the president.

219
00:18:16,678 --> 00:18:17,805
Yes, sir.

220
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:24,603
[suspenseful music continues]

221
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:33,403
[tense music playing]

222
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:46,458
I'll make sure to settle everything.

223
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:50,337
We need to put an end
to Carillo's evil schemes.

224
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,922
["Manindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

225
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,552
[in Arabic] In the protection of Allah.

226
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:00,681
[in Tausug] Thank you.

227
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,603
[in Arabic] May Allah reward you
with goodness.

228
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:13,610
♪ <i>The morning is dark</i>
<i>Opening my eyes after a blink</i> ♪

229
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:17,364
♪ <i>The throne of a tyrant playing king</i> ♪

230
00:19:17,447 --> 00:19:18,740
- [car door closes]
- ♪ <i>Will be set on fire</i> ♪

231
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:21,285
♪ <i>The crown will be reclaimed</i> ♪

232
00:19:21,368 --> 00:19:23,996
♪ <i>It will be returned</i>
<i>To where it came from</i> ♪

233
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:26,540
♪ <i>Everything has its end</i> ♪

234
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:29,877
♪ <i>Evil will come to an end</i> ♪

235
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:32,087
- [line ringing]
- ♪ <i>If justice is only for a select few</i> ♪

236
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:34,840
Madam President,
[in Arabic] peace be upon you.

237
00:19:35,591 --> 00:19:37,050
I'm on my way.

238
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,178
We need to talk.

239
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,762
It's urgent.

240
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:44,183
♪ <i>I refuse to be used anymore</i>
<i>Enough is enough</i> ♪

241
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:48,437
♪ <i>I won't be afraid, I won't back down</i>
<i>I will fight</i> ♪

242
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:52,774
♪ <i>I will stand strong</i> ♪

243
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:54,776
♪ <i>The situation</i> ♪

244
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,320
- [phone ringing]
- ♪ <i>Is harder now</i> ♪

245
00:19:56,403 --> 00:19:57,863
♪ <i>An ally became</i> ♪

246
00:19:57,946 --> 00:19:59,114
General.

247
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:00,782
General.

248
00:20:02,159 --> 00:20:03,619
Awaiting your order, sir.

249
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:09,082
Execute.

250
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:14,296
♪ <i>If justice is only for a select few</i> ♪

251
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:18,967
♪ <i>And justice comes with a price</i> ♪

252
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:21,720
<i>♪ I will no longer stay silent ♪</i>

253
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:24,681
♪ <i>I refuse to be used anymore</i>
<i>Enough is enough</i> ♪

254
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:28,769
♪ <i>I won't be afraid, I won't back down</i>
<i>I will fight</i> ♪

255
00:20:28,852 --> 00:20:32,064
♪ <i>I will stand strong</i> ♪

256
00:20:32,147 --> 00:20:34,650
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [digital trilling]

257
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,398
[in Arabic] You are our Protector,

258
00:21:14,481 --> 00:21:16,858
so give us victory
over the disbelieving people.

259
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:25,701
[whirring]

260
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:30,998
[car engine revving]

261
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:33,125
[explosion]

262
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:36,044
[both grunt] Argh!

263
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:42,759
Sir Mustapha!

264
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:48,140
[fire crackling]

265
00:21:56,690 --> 00:22:00,068
[suspenseful music continues]

266
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:15,125
[suspenseful music playing]

267
00:22:17,627 --> 00:22:21,214
I thought I'd found out
who was responsible

268
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:23,300
<i>for blowing up MV Doña Emilia.</i>

269
00:22:23,383 --> 00:22:25,343
[Marcus] <i>But they killed Sir Mustapha.</i>

270
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,638
[Marcus] <i>I keep on letting Gabriel down.</i>

271
00:22:28,722 --> 00:22:30,140
Man, that's not true.

272
00:22:30,223 --> 00:22:33,310
[Jalil] <i>We'll continue to seek justice</i>
<i>for your brother.</i>

273
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:34,978
This will all be over.

274
00:22:35,062 --> 00:22:37,522
Espina and Marcus are working together.

275
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:39,357
They are ruining our plans.

276
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:41,026
We're so close.

277
00:22:41,109 --> 00:22:44,154
Anyone who might ruin our plan
needs to be gone!

278
00:22:44,237 --> 00:22:46,531
It's Felix. I've been skeptical
about him for some time.

279
00:22:46,615 --> 00:22:49,701
Lara just convinced me
to give him another chance.

280
00:22:51,036 --> 00:22:52,287
What will you do now?

281
00:22:52,370 --> 00:22:53,663
Sir Mustapha is gone.

282
00:22:53,747 --> 00:22:55,207
- They can--
- I'm fine.

283
00:22:55,290 --> 00:22:57,125
Why not just tell Marcus?

284
00:22:57,209 --> 00:23:00,003
If I get exposed,
I'd rather go down alone.

285
00:23:00,087 --> 00:23:01,463
[Jalil]
<i>I can't afford to drag him with me.</i>

286
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:04,633
Our Presidential Chief of Staff
has been ambushed.

287
00:23:04,716 --> 00:23:05,759
[Marcus] <i>You know who you are.</i>

288
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:07,427
Hide while you can.

289
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:10,806
We will not rest
until you're rotting in jail.
